{{Infobox settlement <!--See the Table at Infobox Settlement for all fields and descriptions of usage--> <!-- Basic info ----------------> | official_name = Kwale | native_name = Utagba Ogbe | other_name = | settlement_type = [[City]] <!-- images and maps -----------> | image_skyline = | imagesize = | image_caption = | image_flag = | image_seal = | image_shield = | nickname = | image_map = | map_caption = | pushpin_map = Nigeria<!-- the name of a location map as per http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Template:Location_map --> | pushpin_label_position = bottom | pushpin_map_caption = Location in Nigeria f| coordinates = {{coord|6|11|52.23|N|6|43|42.48|E|region:NG|display=inline,title}} <!-- Location ------------------> | subdivision_type = Country | subdivision_name = {{flag|Nigeria}} | subdivision_type1 = [[States of Nigeria|State]] | subdivision_name1 = [[Delta State]] | subdivision_type2 = [[Local Government Areas of Nigeria|LGA(s)]] | subdivision_name2 = | established_title = <!-- Settled --> | established_date = | leader_title = | leader_name = <!-- Area ---------------------> | unit_pref = <!--Enter: Imperial, if Imperial (metric) is desired--> | area_total_km2 = 268<!-- ALL fields dealing with a measurements are subject to automatic unit conversion--> | area_land_km2 = <!--See table @ Template:Infobox Settlement for details on automatic unit conversion--> | area_water_km2 = | elevation_footnotes = <!--for references: use<ref> </ref> tags--> | elevation_m = <!-- Population -----------------------> | population_footnotes = <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nigerianstat.gov.ng/nbsapps/Connections/Pop2006.pdf |format=PDF |title=FEDERAL REPUBLIC OF NIGERIA : 2006 Population Census |publisher=Web.archive.org |accessdate=25 July 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120305101910/http://www.nigerianstat.gov.ng/nbsapps/Connections/Pop2006.pdf |archivedate=5 March 2012 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> | population_total = | population_as_of = 2006 census | population_est = 176,060<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.citypopulation.de/php/nigeria-admin.php?adm1id=NGA010 | title=Delta (state, Nigeria) | publisher=population.de | accessdate=25 July 2016}}</ref> | pop_est_as_of = 2011 | population_density_km2 = auto <!-- General information ---------------> | timezone = | utc_offset = | timezone_DST = | utc_offset_DST = <!-- Area/postal codes & others --------> | postal_code_type = <!-- enter ZIP code, Postcode, Post code, Postal code... --> | postal_code = | area_code = | blank_name = [[Köppen climate classification|Climate]] | blank_info = [[Tropical savanna climate|Aw]] | website = }} '''Kwale''' is a town in [[Delta State]], Nigeria and is located within the colonial Warri province. Kwale is also considered as a city especially considering it oil and gas reserves, its location all of which can be utilized to transform the town and neighbouring areas into becoming a city. Kwale is host to oil and gas companies some of which have presence in different parts of the African city such as at Ebedei in Umukwata area and at Umusadege <ref name=ThisDay>{{cite web|url=https://www.thisdaylive.com/index.php/2018/03/23/mart-oil-resources-launches-new-brand-identity |title=Mart oil resources launches new brand identity|date=March 23, 2018 |accessdate=April 21, 2018|publisher=ThisDay}}</ref> .
There are considerations about the establishment of modular refineries within the area <ref name=TheNation>{{cite web|url=http://thenationonlineng.net/delta-build-three-modular-refineries/ |title=Delta to build three modular refineries |date=February 22, 2018|accessdate=April 21, 2018|publisher=TheNation}}</ref> . and if ever a separate state is created for the Delta Ibos, Kwale city will become the Warri of the new state. There is a township stadium in the area as well as elementary and secondary schools which services the educational needs of the area.
