'''Las Palmas''' is a [[rocket launch]] site in [[Argentina]] at {{coord|27.13|S|58.75|W}} used on November 12, 1966,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.astronautix.com/sites/lasalmas.htm |title=Las Palmas |website=Astronautix.com |date= |accessdate=2016-01-09}}</ref> for the launch of two [[Titus rocket]]s<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.astronautix.com/lvs/titus.htm |title=Titus |website=Astronautix.com |date= |accessdate=2016-01-09 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303170838/http://www.astronautix.com/lvs/titus.htm |archivedate=2016-03-03 |df= }}</ref> for observing a [[solar eclipse]].

