ster)|New Broadcasting House]] || [[Manchester]] || [[BBC North West]] (1981-2011) || [[BBC Radio Manchester]] (1975-2011) || Previously also home to [[BBC Manchester]] Network Production Unit, [[BBC Philharmonic]] and BBC Religion and Ethics department |- | Dickenson Road Studios || {{sort|Manchester, Rusholme|[[Rusholme]], Manchester}} || [[BBC North]] (1954-1975) || || Former base of [[Mancunian Films]] |- | [[Longsight Free Christian Church]] || {{sort|Manchester, Longsight|[[Longsight]], Manchester}} || || || Outside broadcast unit garage |- | Old Broadcasting House || {{sort|Manchester, Piccadilly|Piccadilly, [[Manchester]]}} || [[BBC North West]] (1929-1981) || || |- | Broadcasting House || [[Newcastle upon Tyne|Newcastle]] || [[BBC North East and Cumbria]] || || |- | St. Catherine's Close || [[Norwich]] || [[BBC East]] || || Base for the BBC regional service in the East of England from 1956 to 2003, prior to the service moving to [[The Forum, Norwich|The Forum]]. |- | South Western House || [[Southampton]] || [[BBC South]] (1961-1991) || [[BBC Radio Solent]] (1970-1991) || Former railway hotel occupied by BBC South until move into Broadcasting House (Southampton) in 1991.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hackett|first=Steve|title=BBC South History|url=http://www2.tv-ark.org.uk/bbcsouth/bbcsouthmain1.html|publisher=TVARK: The Online Television Museum|accessdate=9 February 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120304034441/http://www2.tv-ark.org.uk/bbcsouth/bbcsouthmain1.html|archivedate=4 March 2012|df=}} Contains video footage from ''[[South Today]]'' immediately following the move and ten years later.</ref> |- | Kingswood Warren || [[Tadworth]], Surrey || || || Home to [[BBC Research]], and its predecessors, between 1948 and 2010.<ref>{{cite web|title=BBC Buildings - Kingswood Warren|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/historyofthebbc/collections/buildings/kingswood_warren.shtml|work=The BBC Story|publisher=BBC|accessdate=9 February 2012}}</ref> |}
