{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers'' merchandise}} {{refimprove|date=June 2015}}
Much merchandise has arisen from the Disney tv series ''Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers'' starting in 1989 with various types of stickers, figurines, and McDonald's happy meals toys and, as of now, ending in 2017 with some plush toys and Disney's Tsum Tsums. In between these years there have been a myriad of different types of merchandise including VHS tapes, DVDs, videogames, books, albums, kitchenware, clothes, pins and other various knick knacks.
==Home video releases==
===VHS releases=== On February 22, 1991, [[Walt Disney Home Video]] released 10 select episodes from the series on five [[VHS]] cassettes in the United States, containing a pair of episodes each. {| class="wikitable" |- ! VHS Name !! Episode Titles !! Release Date |- | Double Trouble || style="text-align:center;"|"Dale Beside Himself" & "Flash the Wonder Dog" || February 22, 1991 |- | Crimebusters || style="text-align:center;"|"Catteries Not Included" & "Piratsy Under the Seas" || February 22, 1991 |- | Undercover Critters || style="text-align:center;"|"Adventures in Squirrelsitting" & "Three Men and a Booby" || February 22, 1991 |- | Danger Rangers || style="text-align:center;"|"Kiwi's Big Adventure" & "Bearing Up Baby" || February 22, 1991 |- | Super Sleuths || style="text-align:center;"|"Pound of the Baskervilles" & "Out to Launch" || February 22, 1991 |}
In October 5, 1993 Disney released a VHS containing Halloween specials, for the upcoming holiday season. The specials it featured were from the company’s four arguably most popular series at the time, ''Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers'', ''[[Darkwing Duck]]'', ''[[DuckTales]]'' and ''[[Goof Troop]]''.
The ''Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers'' episode "Ghost of a Chance" was released together with the ''[[Goof Troop]]'' episode "Hallow-Weenies" on one VHS cassette as a special release called ''Boo-Busters''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Disney-Boo-Busters-VHS/dp/6302794226 |title=Disney / Boo-Busters [VHS&#93;: Boo-Busters: Movies & TV |publisher=Amazon.com |date= |accessdate=2013-11-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lib.muohio.edu/multifacet/record/mu3ugb3984136 |title=Boo-busters / [Walt Disney Company&#93; &#124; Miami University Libraries |publisher=Lib.muohio.edu |date= |accessdate=2013-11-08}}</ref> And the ''Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers'' episode "Good Times, Bat Times" was released together with the ''[[Darkwing Duck]]'' episode "Ghoul of My Dreams" on one VHS cassette as a special release called ''Witcheroo!''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Witcheroo-VHS/dp/6302794242 |title=Witcheroo [VHS&#93;: Witcheroo: Movies & TV |publisher=Amazon.com |date= |accessdate=2013-11-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lib.muohio.edu/multifacet/record/mu3ugb4018981 |title=Witcheroo! / Walt Disney Company &#124; Miami University Libraries |publisher=Lib.muohio.edu |date= |accessdate=2013-11-08}}</ref>
Several other episodes were available on international releases.
====UK, Australia & New Zealand releases==== Eleven VHS cassettes containing 23 episodes of the series were released in the United Kingdom, Australia and New Zealand. {| class="wikitable" |- ! VHS Name !! Episode Titles !! Release Date |- | Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers (Volume 1): Double Trouble || style="text-align:center;"|"Piratsy Under the Seas" & "Catteries Not Included" || September 11, 1992 |- | Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers (Volume 2): The Pound of the Baskervilles || style="text-align:center;"|"Pound of the Baskervilles" & "Adventures in Squirrelsitting" || September 11, 1992 |- | Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers (Volume 3): Risky Beesness || style="text-align:center;"|"Bearing Up Baby" & "Risky Beesness" || September 11, 1992 |- | Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers (Volume 4): Crimebusters || style="text-align:center;"|"Dale Beside Himself" & "Flash the Wonder Dog" || September 11, 1992 |- | Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers (Volume 5): Out to Launch || style="text-align:center;"|"Out to Launch" & "The Carpetsnaggers" || September 11, 1992 |- | Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers (Volume 6): 3 Men and a Birdie || style="text-align:center;"|"Three Men and a Booby" & "Parental Discretion Retired" || April 2, 1993 |- | Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers (Volume 7): Ghouls and Jewels || style="text-align:center;"|"Ghost of a Chance" & "A Wolf in Cheap Clothing" || April 2, 1993 |- | Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers (Volume 8): Half-Size Heroes || style="text-align:center;"|"A Lad in a Lamp" & "Seer No Evil" || April 2, 1993 |- | Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers (Volume 9): Flies in Disguise || style="text-align:center;"|"Chocolate Chips", "Gorilla My Dreams" & "A Creep in the Deep" || September 10, 1993 |- | Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers (Volume 10): Danger Rangers || style="text-align:center;"|"Out of Scale" & "Kiwi's Big Adventure" || September 10, 1993 |- | Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers (Volume 11): Duelling Dale || style="text-align:center;"|"Mind Your Cheese and Q's" & "The S.S. Drainpipe" || September 10, 1993 |}
===DVD releases===
====US (Region 1)==== [[Walt Disney Studios Home Entertainment]] has released some of the series on DVD; two volumes have been released in Region 1 thus far featuring the first 51 episodes of the series. The first was released on November 8, 2005 (containing episodes 1-27) and the second on November 14, 2006 (containing episodes 28-51).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com/Chip-Rescue-Rangers-Tress-MacNeille/dp/B000AXWGRM |title=Amazon.com: Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers - Volume 1 |publisher=Amazon.com |accessdate=2013-04-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com/Chip-Rescue-Rangers-Tress-MacNeille/dp/B000HWZ4RA |title=Amazon.com: Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers - Volume 2 |publisher=Amazon.com |accessdate=2013-04-01}}</ref> The episodes on the first volume are arranged by production date, while the episodes on the second volume are arranged by original air date. The sets were packaged in a box containing 3 slipcases, one for each disc. There has yet to be any word from Disney regarding the release of a third volume set for episodes 52-65.
{| class="wikitable sortable" |- ! DVD Name !! Ep # !! Release date |- | Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers: Volume 1 || style="text-align:center;"|27 || November 8, 2005 |- | Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers: Volume 2 || style="text-align:center;"|24 || November 14, 2006 |- | Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers: Volume 3 || style="text-align:center;"|14 || TBA |}
====International (Region 2)==== In the United Kingdom, Disney released one Region 2 volume in 2007, titled ''Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers First Collection''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/Chip-Dale-Rescue-Rangers-Collection/dp/B000M2E7GE|title=Chip N Dale - Rescue Rangers - First Collection - 3 Disc Set DVD: Amazon.co.uk: Chip 'n' Dale Rescue Rangers: Film & TV |publisher=Amazon.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2012-10-17}}</ref> Despite the set being similar to the US version, the DVD contained only 20 episodes, while having 6 language tracks: English, French, Dutch, German, Spanish and Italian. Several other similar releases were then made to other countries, but only going up to episode #20. On December 5, 2012, a second DVD set of the series was released in the UK, but as a Region 2 version of Volume 2, titled ''Chip n Dale Rescue Rangers Season 2''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/Chip-Dale-Rescue-Rangers-Season/dp/B009KYYARQ/ref=sr_1_2?ie=UTF8&qid=1352747954&sr=8-2 |title=Chip N Dale Rescue Rangers Season 2 [DVD] |deadurl=no |accessdate=2012-11-16}}</ref> Unlike the first DVD, this 3-disc set includes a Fastplay mode and only two language tracks: English and German, but subtitles have not been added. As of yet, there are no plans to release the rest of the series, or the seven episodes missing between the first two sets.
{| class="wikitable sortable" |- ! DVD Name !! Ep # !! Release date !! Language |- | Walt Disney's Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers, First Collection || style="text-align:center;"|20 || February 12, 2007 || English, French, Dutch, German, Spanish and Italian |- | Walt Disney's Chip 'n Dale Rescue Rangers - Season 2 || style="text-align:center;"|24 || December 5, 2012 || English and German |}
