'''PM2FGG''' (101.0 FM), on-air name '''Jak 101 FM''' or '''Jak FM''', is an [[adult contemporary radio]] station in [[Jakarta]], Indonesia. In 2015, Jak FM held 6% radio market share.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mari.co.id/news/press-release/read/6/mari-go-public-/?l=2|title=MARI GO PUBLIC! Penawaran perdana 2-4 Februari 2016|first=Mahaka Radio|last=Integra|website=mari.co.id}}</ref> The radio company, PT Suara Irama Indah, was the first commercial FM radio station in the country.
{{Infobox radio station | name = PM2FGG | image = | image_size = <!-- optional when used with image parameter, specifies image size --> | alt = <!-- optional when used with image parameter, specifies image alternate (alt) text --> | caption = <!-- optional when used with image parameter, specifies image caption --> | city = [[Central Jakarta]], [[DKI Jakarta]] | area = [[Jabodetabek]] metropolitan area, some | branding = '''Jak 101 FM''' | slogan = "Memainkan musik terbaik di Jakarta" (English: plays best music in Jakarta) | frequency = [[101.0 MHz]] | airdate = around late 1970s (possibly 1976), as '''Jak FM''': [[2006 in radio|2006]] | format = [[Adult contemporary]] radio | language = Indonesian | power = 10 kW | class = B | former_frequencies = 101.25 FM | affiliations = [[Erick Thohir]] | operator = Masima Radio (1980s-2006), Mahaka Group (2006-present) through PT Radio Suara Irama Indah | owner = Mahaka Radio Integra (MARI) | sister_stations = [[PM2FGU|Gen 98.7 FM]], [[PM2FAW|Hot 93.2 FM]], [[PM2FHF|Mustang 88.0 FM]], [[PM2FHN|Kis 95.1 FM]], [[Most Radio]] 105.8 FM | webcast = | website = http://www.jak101fm.com }}
==History== ===Suara Irama Indah era=== After [[PM2FGZ|Elshinta Radio]] was bought (possibly by [[Salim Group]]) in the late 1970s, Soejoso Karsono created Radio Suara Irama Indah.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://historia.id/persona/articles/the-singing-commodore-DLQwv|title=The Singing Commodore|website=Historia - Obrolan Perempuan Urban}}</ref> Sudibyo Karsono also contributed to Irama Indah radio<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sutarko.blogspot.co.id/2011/05/sudibyo-karsono-dan-hidroponik-serius.html|title=Sudibyo Karsono dan Hidroponik Serius|website=sutarko.blogspot.co.id}}</ref>. Later the radio changed into B-FM and Radio One in the late 1980s. ===Radio One=== Radio One started broadcasting in late 1980s. This radio's audience was young adults, playing classical music. With affiliation to [[Prambors]] group in late 1980's, Radio One was partially owned by Masima Group along with sister station [[PM2FGK|Prambors]], Delta FM, Female Radio (acquisition of [[Tangerang]]-located station), Bahana 101.8, M97 (now RDI) and SPFM (now Oz Radio). Radio One once had provincial stations, but they were sold to Masima to create Prambors provincial stations. In 2007, this affiliation led to ownership of Masima Group's 20% share by Mahaka Group. In 2004, the 101.0 FM frequency was first time used, after using 101.25 FM for over a decade. In 2006, management decided to change Radio One branding into 101 Jak FM. Ownership was overtaken by Mahaka group and now they are the sole operators. ===Jak FM === Jak FM changed the branding only. Neither DJ's nor music was altered from Radio One. To cater younger and more varied listeners, Jak FM later added new music, mostly Western music. Jak FM slowly reduced [[Classic hits|classic hits]] and added new announcers, including morning show DJ Ronal Surapradja and Tike Prie. ==Programming== Jak FM operates for 18 hours (06.00 (all time in [[UTC+7]])-00.00) . Outside operating hours, Jak FM plays automated music. Daily programs include:
* Sarapan Seru (Ronal, Tike, Melissa Karim) * 101 Menit Musik Nonstop (various announcers) * Jak Best Music (various announcers) * Joki 3 In 1 (Jodi, Vecky) - based on abandoned 3-in-1 policy in Jakarta main avenues * Night Mix (various announcers) ==References== {{reflist}}
{{Asia topic|List of radio stations in}} {{Jakarta Radio}}
